ps is often a less boring way to level (or powerlevel).  On raids, I would never play two at the same time unless one was a necro/mage/ench, etc.  I can see possibly playing two clerics together, in a CH line, it would not be difficult, but it really wouldn't be any more fun.<br>
<br>
I have a 50 warrior with 3 days /played using a shaman on second computer to PL.  I lost interest in the warrior and have not played him in a while, especially since my guild has more than enough 60 warriors.  Nowadays I play my 60 Rogue (non-powerleveled primary) and 53 Cleric together as much as possible for exp.  I've found it the ideal combination in places like Fungus Grove where there are many mobs that cast (just whip around and backstab while they cast).  If I really want to grind for exp on the Rogue I de-group the two, however I've been working on getting the cleric to 60 so I usually keep them grouped.<br>
<br>
Rogue/Cleric is a very playable combo in groups also.  Being a melee in combat, I always know how many mobs are pulled and who they are attacking.  Playing only a cleric, one might not be as aware of the situation.  I've played the two together in just about every high level dungeon, and it's very easy.  I'd say I only loose maybe 2 - 5% of overall damage output due to lost backstabs.  Backstab damage accounts for roughly 35% of our overall damage output (hence the 50% advantage over warrior damage) and I miss maybe 5 - 10% of the backstabs due to casting heals. <br>
<br>
My setup is two monitors, one keyboard and mouse, and a kvm switch that uses CTRL-CTRL-1 or 2 to switch computers.  This is possibly less optimal than two keyboards and two mice, but it really messes up my back after twisting around to another keyboard for more than a few hours at a time.  It's a belkin switch, in case you're interested.<br>
<br>
Hope this helps anyone interested in doing this.<br>
 <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12460>Kahdius Ka`tan</a><br>Assassin of Karana<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ubloodshard.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bloodshard</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/28/01 4:27:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://server3002.freeyellow.com/oggs/Bldshrdhead.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> /shiver</span><hr size=1> Sorry, don't like multi-played characters. Thanak sumed up most of my reasons. <br>
<br>
On your typical raid people's attention drop. Everyone is not at 100 precent so then your 80/20 attention span is now a 70/10 or worse. <br>
<br>
Sorry, just not into it. Reminds me of the guy that brings 2 characters 2 a D&amp;D game &amp; insists on playing them both. Sure, it keeps the player busy but in the end those characters loose something of their soul.<br>
<br>
/shrug Guess I'm too much of a roleplayer at heart. <br>
<br>
Also, I like the interaction with other people. Even if it's to laugh because we're grouped with a clueless person. I can loose a little xps for a good laugh. Some of the friends I've met on line more then make up for it. And many times those are people I wouldn't have gotten to know if their role was taken up by my 2nd PC. <br>
